latestPosts.caption:
A long overdue appreciation post and a late wedding shoutout!

Thank you for being that one constant friend I could always turn to, no matter the time or situation. Through my lowest moments, you were always there. Whether I was having the worst days or celebrating the best, you stood by me.

You truly played the part of a girlfriend on my wedding day, supportive, present, and exactly who I needed by my side. Thank you for being there for me in every way. For listening to all my worries, rants, anxious spirals, and breakdowns without ever offering advice I didn’t ask for, just being there with an open heart and ears. That meant more than you know.

Being a best friend doesn’t mean talking every day or seeing each other constantly. You’ve shown me that real friendship goes beyond that. You’ll always hold such a meaningful place in my life, the one I can always count on.

I’m so happy to see you step into this beautiful new chapter. Wishing you all the success and love in both your career and your personal life. I know you’re going to thrive in every way, just like you always do.

Can’t wait to host you and Ruchi at home soon! Wishing you both a very happy married life and all the best as you begin this journey together.

Love you, best friend. Thank you for everything♥️

#bestfriend #bffs #wedding #bestfriendswedding
